   "body" : "There has been talk before (and I'm surprised to not find an existing issue about it) of having different memory usage profiles. This could encompass defaults for:\r\n* `-dbcache`\r\n* `-par`\r\n* `-maxsigcachesize`\r\n* `-maxmempool`\r\n* `-maxorphantx`\r\n* `-maxconnections`\r\n* `-maxreceivebuffer`\r\n* `-maxsendbuffer`\r\n\r\nFor desktop systems, autodetecting could be used to determine optimal settings. For servers, it could be specified on the command line. I have heard about interest in a means for specifying \"Just use all the memory I have\".",
